Results.ReviewText: I have bought Nescafe for 40 years. Then you changed the taste and I now hate it!! I have changed to a supermarket brand now. Not as nice as the ORIGINAL Nescafe either but at least it is cheaper and nicer than the new Nescafe. I stocked up on the old Nescafe and still have enough for a few more days. Results.ReviewText:
Nescafe is Flavoursome, smooth, aromatic, and comforting.  I enjoy a Nescafe with friends, or relaxing alone, reading a good book or just having some me time.
Nescafe is of such good quality that you don't need to use too much to taste the comforting flavour of each cup.  This makes the already great value for money coffee, last much longer than expected, and therefore, making me an even happier customer.  I would never drink any other coffee because Nescafes taste, value for money and quality cannot be beaten.
Results.Title: just the very best

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks very much for leaving your thoughts!

Results.ReviewText: Have been put off Nescafe and most instant coffee by the constant tinkering that goes on with the recipe, so that a brand you've enjoyed in the past will taste completely different (and usually much worse) when you go to buy it again.  Several brands now produce really good real coffee bags which are as convenient to use as a tea bag, and although more expensive than instant, are consistently good quality.  I drink less coffee but of better quality now, and cannot see myself going back to Nescafe instant.
Results.Title: Sorry, not for me.

Results.ReviewText: I used to only use cheap coffee as that was all I could afford at the time but thought I would treat myself to nescafe while I was shopping,it was also on promotion which made it even more appealing to me,I never really entertained nescafe before because I always thought it looked to strong 4me but boy was I wrong the minute I tasted it for the 1st time I've never looked back and u may not believe this but the family enjoy it to,regardless wether on promotion or not it's now 1st on my shopping list.
Results.Title: Happy as larry

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk Nescafe original for far more years than i care to remember,and there has never been an equal,or another brand that i would think of switching to,BUT since the introduction of the Red top,and slight adaptation,i find the taste less endearing to my palate,at present i have no intention of trying other brands,though i do now drink significantly less Nescafe Coffee,due to the change in taste,and i agree with others,this should not be sold as original Nescafe,because clearly,it isn't.
Results.Title: why try to fix whats not broke

Results.ReviewText: You simply cannot beat Nescafe coffee for flavour. I enjoy a strong cup of coffee and find Nescafe is perfect for this, and it doesn't have that bitter after taste you get with so many designer coffees. I've been drinking Nescafe forever and have tried so many different brands but always go back to Nescafe. It really does have the nicest flavour and a wonderful aroma, the one you love to smell first thing in the morning. If you love a good cup of coffee then I highly recommend you try Nescafe.
Results.Title: Still my favourite ♥

I have been a consumer of the original Nescafé all of my life. This is a product that I will always associate with my 21 blissful years I have been with my husband who has never failed to make me a morning cuppa in.
In all of that time, I have never had the heart to tell him that the meaningful " I love you" that always follows him kissing me on the forehead after handing me the coffee is directed to the steaming cup rather than him!!
(Only joking, I love just as much!!!)
Great product x
Results.Title: 21 year anniversary

Results.ReviewText: Nescafé original red cap is the perfect cuppa for me.Ive been drinking coffee for over 30yrs, I've tried many other coffee's but none compare to Nescafé original, some coffee can give me an upset stomach, has either a bitter taste or hardly any taste at all, Nescafé original is just right.I didn't think it could be improved but along with the new red cap came an even better smoother taste and I love it.All other family members share this view, so well done Nescafé, it's a winner in my eyes.
Results.Title: Perfect

Results.ReviewText:
I have been buying Nescafe Original for many years now.  Although occasionally I try other brands, my family prefer the smooth, rich flavour of this brand.
Although a little expensive, the quality of this long established coffee is second to none.  It's the first drink I wake up to and the last before going to bed. I prefer adding a dash of semi-skimmed milk, but not too much.  The richer the better!  Nescafe Original is the brand others try to emulate, but they're not as good!  Try it!
Results.Title: Savour the Aroma!

Results.ReviewText: I must admit I am a bit of a Nescafe nut. It has been my Coffee of choice for longer than I can remember, but in saying that I really do feel its lost some of its strength. It's still has that wonderful aromatic punch when you first open the jar, but alas this doesn't last for as long as it used too, and I think this lack of staying power is picked up in the taste, after a day or two. So although it is still my coffee brand of choice, I really wish it tasted the same as it always did
Results.Title: lost some of its flavour

Results.ReviewText: After all the coffee I've had (granulated form), I have to say I find Nescafe Original to be the best tasting of them all. We wouldn't have any other at home.
Results.Title: Great Taste !!!

Results.ReviewText: I am a Nescafe Original Fan i find the Ganules have more flavour and depth to the taste and not bitter i do drink my coffee Black, and this may make a difference to taste. The package is great spelling out cearly the coffee and has the full ingridients and contents. There is also a refill in a handy pack now, i tried the Nescafe Fine Blend but it's taste and flavour i thought not as strong.
Results.Title: Whole Ground Taste

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking Nescafe forever!!I would never swap.I stockpile whenever it is on offer somewhere!Nescafe has the perfect blend for a anytime coffee.The bitterness is just right and has a delicious,warming taste with a nice strong pure coffee flavour.The quality for a instant coffee is amazing for the price you pay for a jar,great value for money.My perfect wake me up in the morning drink.It even tastes amazing in a homemade coffee cake.I would never buy any other brand.
Results.Title: My go to coffee

Results.ReviewText:
I grew up watching comedian Benny Hill on TV and one cod Continental phrase, I think, he used (though he spoke perfect French) was "Il fait beau Nescaff!" instead, of course, for "Il fait beau n'est- ce pas?!"
Nescafe hit on a winner with its original, that I used to purchase in tins, and nothing I have experienced in my very many years has come close in matching its inimitable, and consistent, terrific taste apart, not unsurprisingly,  from  Nescafe's own Espresso brand.

Results.ReviewText: I always buy the same Nescafe Original as far back as I can remember and never bought anything else once we ran out and I had to nip to Asda 24 store to get a jar as the taste is the only one that suits my pallet and if you look around you can get it at a very good price which I am not bothered as I would buy it at whatever price it has been. Results.ReviewText: My family have always bought Nescafe and love the great taste.  The coffee is great but we do not like the recent changes to the jar lid. First, the change of colour of the lid caught us off-guard. We nearly bought the wrong coffee (which would have been a disaster!).  Second, the smooth lid (as opposed to the old brown ridged lid) is harder to open and looks cheap.  Please bring back the brown ridged lid!
Results.Title: Nice Flavour But Poor Lid Design

Results.ReviewText: I have always been a Nescafé drinker. The Original has a deep, rich flavour that you do not always get from instant coffee, which is sometimes very bitter. I have never found this with Nescafé.....it is one of few coffees that I can drink black and only being a coffee drinker it is important to me that I am able to enjoy great tasting coffee. I use the decaf blend in the evenings and enjoy that as well.
